quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  22,39,"Permission has been granted{1}to those who are combated{2}, because they have been dealt with unjustly—and most surely Allah is Able to give them support:",1:[Qira’at: All except for Nafie’, Abu Amr, Asem, Abu Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “He has granted permission to those…”],2:[Qira’at: All except for Nafie’, Ibn Amer, Hafs, and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…to those who combat…”]
  22,40,"those who have been unjustifiably evicted from their homes merely for saying, “Our Lord is Allah.” And were it not that Allah repels people by means of others, monasteries and churches and synagogues and mosques—where the name of Allah is mentioned frequently—would have been utterly demolished{1}. And most surely, Allah will support whoever supports Him. Indeed, Allah is certainly All-Powerful, Almighty.",1:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Ibn Kathir, and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…would have been demolished.”]
  22,41,"Those who, when We give them authority in the land, establish the prayer and bring{1}the purifying charity{2}and command to what is fair and forbid what is deplorable. And with Allah rests the outcome of all events.",1:[The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.],2:[The Arabic word used is z<i>akāt</i>, which denotes purification and growth.]
  22,42,"And if they disbelieve you<sup>sg </sup>—so before them the people of Noah andʻĀd{1}and Thamud{2}<i>(also) </i>disbelieved,",1:[The pagan tribe of Prophet Hûd.],2:[The pagan tribe of Prophet Salih.]
  22,43,"and the people of Abraham and the people of Lot,"
  22,44,"and the inhabitants of Midian<i>(as w </i><i>ell). </i>And Moses was disbelieved. So I reprieved the deniers then I seized them, so how terrible was My condemnation?"
  22,45,"So how many a town have We{1}annihilatedwhile it was unjust, so that it lies devastated upon its trellises, with an abandoned well and a lofty mansion?",1:[Qira’at: Abu Amr and Ya’qub read it as: “…have I annihilated…”]
  22,46,"Have they not journeyed in the land and had hearts to reason with or ears to listen with? Therefore, it is not the sight<i>(s) </i>that go blind, but it is the hearts within the chests that go blind."
